result.name: Marugame Seimen

reviews.text: Good quality, and always keep at good standard
Fast food quality udon. Other snacks are also so so. Place not clean.
Great Japanese udon. Love the chewy texture of the thick udon. The tempura were freshly made and not oily. But the soup base was a bit too salty.

A Japanese style eatery. You order your chosen soup and udon and pick the side dishes. Credit and cash accepted. Very simple and fast fare. Lots of seating and not very busy. For a simple and quick lunch or dinner, this is commendable.

Udon restaurant. You can choose your Udon from pure Udon noodle with soy sauce, udon topped with half boiled egg and even mara spicy udon and many more. After ordering udon, you can pick up more side dishes for your appetite as like vege fries, fish cake bar, fried chicken, and sushi. Pay for what you pick up on your plate and find your seat. No one show you your seat.

Udon noodle is very sleek and chewy. They make this noodle at site. All side dishes were well made and delicious.

Don't forget to return your empty tray after enjoyed the meal.

reviews.text: Ispuare最平而食品唔錯食肆，6至70元可以飽肚而回的。
自助形式方便快捷,環境簡潔,可自由選擇拉麵和配料的配搭,食物衞生美味,有身在日本的感覺
日式大眾鸟冬店，(在日本較流行)，在香港的出品尚可，但店内潔淨齊整，坐得舒服。
食物不錯吃！用團購劵更加抵吃！！👍下午茶時段客人不多，坐得舒適自灰！
醬油烏冬加西蘭花，很好味！適合素食者

reviews.text: Isquare  Is a nice shopping mall it has really call art work in front of it. It's really busy has a lot of nice shops that are all open past 10:00 p.m. It's in a convenient location from the Subway. Has some good restaurants in it. And the movie theater

It's a modern and great design shopping center and close to my hotel. I went here for a lunch and found Mark & Spencer on the ground floor and shopped a bit here. Overall, it's a nice shopping center.
Good for shopping (M&S clothing and food hall, marketplace), kids-r-us and other kid brands, very good cinema, linked to TST MTR train station
Visited the EyeLounge.  Very nice location with breath taking views of the city! Good drinks and very nice restaurant and cuisine.
High end shopping mall in Kowloon. Big brands.
